Ņ"FOR FREEDOM
THIS SEAT AND THE PATH LEADING HERETO HAVE BEEN PROVIDED AS A MEMORIAL TO THE MEN OF NUMBERUFALMOUTH COMPANY OF THE HOME GUARD, WHO DURING 1940, 41, 42, 43, 44, AFTER THEIR DAY'S WORK NIGHTLY PATROLLED THIS COAST ARMED AND VIGILANT AGAINST GERMAN LANDINGS.

THUS THEY WATCHED 1000 DAWNS APPEAR ACROSS THESE GREAT WATERS WHICH FORM OUR COUNTRY'S MOAT."¶
